# Blue Nile Men's Bracelets Review {{year}}: Cuban Link, Tennis, Figaro & More, Ranked

Blue Nile's men's bracelet page runs from a $655 sterling silver Cuban link to a $40,570 Blue Nile Signature diamond tennis bracelet. The most reviewed piece — by a wide margin — is the 8" Miami Cuban Link in 14k yellow gold at 6mm and $2,225. The second insight most buyers miss: the lab-grown diamond tennis bracelet at 30% off with disclosed F-G / VS2-SI1 quality is the strongest value purchase on this page.

Before the rankings, one thing I need to say about width selection: **width and length interact.** A 15mm wide Cuban link bracelet sits higher on the wrist than a 6mm one, compresses the skin more, and needs the same nominal length to achieve the same drape. If you're buying a Cuban wider than 9mm, measure your wrist while slightly flexed — the bracelet needs to accommodate your wrist at its widest position during everyday movement.

---

