## Miami Cuban Link: The Anchor of Men's Fine Bracelets

The Miami Cuban is the most reviewed chain style on Blue Nile's men's page. Flat, interlocking, slightly twisted oval links — the design defined hip-hop jewelry culture in the 1990s and has since become genuinely mainstream fine jewelry. Blue Nile carries it in five widths — 6mm, 7.3mm, 9.3mm, 11mm, and 15mm — plus a 9" length option at 11mm.

[![Men's Miami Cuban link bracelet in 14k yellow gold, Blue Nile lifestyle photo](/images/mens-miami-cuban-link-bracelet-yellow-gold.avif)](/images/mens-miami-cuban-link-bracelet-yellow-gold.avif)

**The 6mm Cuban: Most Reviewed, Best Starting Point (7 Reviews)**

The [8" Miami Cuban Link in 14k Yellow Gold at 6mm](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/bracelets/8-mens-miami-cuban-link-bracelet-in-14k-yellow-gold-6-mm-item-193159?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) at $2,225 has 7 verified reviews — the most of any piece on the page. Seven reviews at full price with no discount tells you buyers return to rate this because they're satisfied. This is the entry point to the Cuban link in fine gold: visible, substantial, but not overwhelming on most wrist sizes.

> **Farzana's Expert Take:** At $2,225 for 14k yellow gold with 7 reviews, the 6mm Cuban is the benchmark men's gold bracelet at Blue Nile. If you're buying a man a first fine gold bracelet and don't know his exact preference, this is the piece with the highest buyer-confidence signal on the page.

